The All Progressives Congress (APC) in Jigawa state is on its path of winning majority of the 30 seats of the State House of Assembly as it has already won all the 23 seats so far announced. The following are the names of the winners and their scores at the State House of Assembly election held on Saturday: Gagarawa LGA Ibrahim Husaini Kadeta, APC – 15,405 Mutari Ibrahim Gonga, PDP   –   8,368  Buji LGA Sale Baba,  –       APC – 21,297 Isa Bello Gwadayi, PDP – 9,312  Guri LGA Suleiman Musa Kadira, APC – 20,851 Muhammad Umar,         PDP –  7,346  Gwiwa LGA Aminu Zakari,            APC – 20,207 Isah Alasan Korayal, APC –  7,674  Kanya constituency in Babura LGA Usman H. Isah,   APC – 17,321 Mansur Danladi, PDP – 4.375  Kazaure LGA Bala Hamza Gada, APC – 21,505 Zakari Tura,               PDP – 3,105  Kirikasamma LGA Aliyu Ahmad Aliyu,  –  APC – 26,109 Abdu Muhammad,  –  PDP –  9,223  Gumel LGA Sani Isiyaku,  –   APC – 15,709 Aliyu Muh’d,  –   PDP –  4,907  Auyo LGA Ishaq Sani,                 APC – 27,487 Haruna Bako Uzza,   PDP –   7,766  Bulangu constuency, Kafin Hausa LGA Yusif Ahmed Soja Bulangu, APC – 14,886 Muhd Abdullahi Bulangu,     SDP –  7,327  Kafin Hausa LGA Adamu Babanbare       APC – 22,585 Yahaya Yusuf Dumadumin Kyaure,  PDP –  7,266  Taura LGA Dayyabu Shehu,      APC – 32,216 Lawan Idi Kwalam, PDP – 11,528  Hadejia LGA Abubakar Sadiq Muh’d, APC – 25,383 Suleiman Dawaki,          PDP –   6,030  Kaugama LGA Sani Sale, APC – 23,481  Mallam Madori LGA Kais Abdullah,     –  APC – 27,400 Muhd Nagaru,   –   PDP  – 7,432  Dutse LGA Musa Sule Dutse,      APC – 43,176 Shehu Umar Chamo, PDP – 14,483  Ringim LGA Aminu Sule Sankara,        APC – 41,458 Murtala Abubakar Muh’d, PDP – 27,864  Gwaram Constituency, Gwaram LGA Isah Idris,          APC – 31,713 Abubakar Sani, PDP  –   7,343  Fagam constituency, Gwaram LGA Shuaibu Inuwa,  APC  –  26,312 Hannafi Yakubu, PDP  –  4,911  Babura constituency, Babura LGA Kabiru Isah, APC – 26,043 Isah Ubale,  PDP –  4,610  Sule 